.TH "memory_map_bottom_up" 9 "memory_map_bottom_up" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
memory_map_bottom_up \- Map [map_start, map_end) bottom up
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" memory_map_bottom_up
.BI "(unsigned long map_start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long map_end "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "map_start" 12
start address of the target memory range
.IP "map_end" 12
end address of the target memory range
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will setup direct mapping for memory range
[map_start, map_end) in bottom-up. Since we have limited the
bottom-up allocation above the kernel, the page tables will
be allocated just above the kernel and we map the memory
in [map_start, map_end) in bottom-up.
